Gurjars (Gujjars) are not regarded as an ethnic group in Pakistan. They are regarded as a diverse and wide-spread tribe, ''biradri'' or community. Gurjars of Pakistan identify mostly as Punjabis, Kashmiris, Sindhis and many other ethnic groups and view themselves as a part of their respective ethnic groups. Gojri might be only spoken by Gurjars, but less than 1 percent of Gurjars speak Gojri or identify it as their language.
